23.01.2020本文字数：2877，阅读时长大约5分钟导读：2020年1月23日，第一财经记者实地探访协和武汉红十字会医院发热门诊。
23.01.2020: 2877 words: 2877, reading for about 5 minutes: January 23, 2020, the first financial reporter field visit Concorde and Wuhan Red Cross Hospital fever clinic.
作者| 第一财经吴绵强周芳陈益刊编辑 | 张富贵为了遏制新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎扩散，按照武汉市新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情防控指挥部通告，自1月23日10时起，武汉全市城市公交、地铁、轮渡、长途客运暂停运营；机场、火车站离汉通道暂时关闭。
Zhang Fuqui, the chief financial officer, has temporarily closed the Han corridor at airports and railway stations since 10: 00 a.m. on January 23, as announced by Wuhan's new-style coronavirus-infected pneumonia command notice that the city's public transport, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger transport has been temporarily closed.
封城后的武汉人，过得怎样？一财记者武汉“封城”首日探访发热门诊Play▲记者：第一财经 吴绵强23日上午10时许，第一财经记者在武汉市红十字医院采访了解到，目前等待检测体温的人群已经排起了长队，医护人员身穿防护服给患者监测体温，导诊台的护士正在忙碌地为前来咨询焦急的患者答疑解惑。
Wuhan after the closure of the city, how well? A reporter Wuhan "closed the city" first day visit fever clinic About 10: 00 am, the first financial reporter in Wuhan City, the first financial reporter to understand that at present waiting to test the body temperature of the people have long queued up, medical staff wearing protective clothing to monitor the temperature of patients, the nurses at the clinic are busy consulting anxious patients.
▲2020年1月23日，协和武汉红十字会医院发热门诊，不断有前来就诊的市民，均戴着口罩。
January 23, 2020, the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital fever clinic, continuous visitors to the public, wearing masks.
▲2020年1月23日，协和武汉红十字会医院发热门诊内，医护人员全副武装对前来问诊的患者检测。
January 23, 2020, the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital fever clinic, medical personnel are fully equipped to visit the patient testing.
▲2020年1月23日，协和武汉红十字会医院发热门诊大厅，众多市民前来问诊和检测。
January 23, 2020, the Wuhan Red Cross Hospital fever clinic hall, a large number of citizens came for medical treatment and testing.
护士告诉记者，目前医院有470张床位，但是还没有住满，大家可以根据病情的轻重缓急来判断，如果症状不是很明显，可以到家里待着自行隔离。
The nurse told reporters there were 470 beds in the hospital, but they were not fully occupied and could be ordered to stay at home if the symptoms were not obvious.
护士同时表示，如果有疑似病例，将会立即送到病房，做隔离处置措施。
The nurse also said that if there is a suspected case, it will be immediately sent to the ward for isolation measures.
市民周先生已经63岁了，需要监测体温，早上7点就过来排队，一直等到现在。
Mr Zhou, a 63-year-old citizen who needs to monitor his temperature, has been queuing up at 7am and waiting until now.
周先生的老伴介绍，丈夫身体不好，有肺部疾病，10天前就出现肺肿，在其他医院无法办理住院，今天才来到这里。
Mr. Zhou's wife introduced that her husband is in poor health, has lung disease, had lung swelling 10 days ago, can not be hospitalized in other hospitals, came here today.
▲2020年1月23日，协和武汉红十字会医院发热门诊内，患者进行信息登记。
On January 23, 2020, the Concorde Wuhan Red Cross Hospital fever clinic, patients carried out information registration.
与普通信息登记不同，这一次信息登记中，除了个人信息之外，还要详细登记住址信息。
Unlike the general information registration, this time the registration of information, in addition to personal information, but also in detail registration address information.
▲2020年1月23日，协和武汉红十字会医院发热门诊内，一名市民趟在大厅的椅子等待就诊。
On January 23, 2020, Concorde Wuhan Red Cross Hospital fever clinic, a citizen waded in the hall chair waiting to see a doctor.
▲2020年1月23日，武汉协和红十字会医院通知，接上级通知，我院暂定为“发热患者定点诊疗医院”。
January 23, 2020, Wuhan Concorde Red Cross Hospital informed that the higher level notification, our hospital provisionally designated as "fever patients in the designated hospital."
即日起，门诊只接诊体温≥37.3°发热患者，其他专科均停诊，非发热患者请到其他医院就诊。
From now on, the outpatient consultation temperature is only 37.3?? fever patient, other specialties are stopped, non-febrile patients please go to other hospitals.
不便之处，敬请谅解。
Please forgive me for any inconvenience caused.
尽量不出门尽量不出门，已经成为不少武汉市民的选择。
Try not to go out as much as possible, has become the choice of many Wuhan city residents.
“我家现在就是不出门。
"My family just doesn't go out now.
”武汉市民乔先生告诉第一财经记者。
Mr Wuhan Min Qiao told the first financial reporter.
刘女士一早喊上老公去超市买东西，买了三购物车的东西，包括蔬菜、肉类等食品，花了2000多元。
Ms. Liu called her husband to the supermarket to buy things, including vegetables, meat and other food, spent more than 2000 yuan.
“后面就留在家里不出去了”。
Stay at home and don't go out.
张女士告诉第一财经记者，自己几天都没有出门了，买菜主要通过某大型生鲜电商平台。
Ms. Zhang told the first financial reporter that he did not go out for a few days, mainly through a large fresh electric business platform.
昨天上午下单1个多小时菜就送到了，晚上想再买点菜，下单送菜已经排到今天晚上9点以后。
Yesterday morning I ordered more than one hour of dishes on the delivery, evening would like to buy some more dishes, orders have been scheduled until after 9 pm today.
王女士和家人已经在家宅了多日，身在外地的丈夫原本计划今日赶回武汉，但在上飞机前却被拦下，航班取消。
Ms. Wang and her family have been at home for days, and her husband, who was outside the city, had planned to travel back to Wuhan today, but was stopped and the flight cancelled before boarding the plane.
她的爸爸一早赶去超市采购。
Her father rushed to the supermarket early in the morning.
“希望生活供给充足，希望疫情尽快得到有效控制！”目前网上也流传着一些超市提高蔬菜价格。
"Hope the supply of life is sufficient, hope that the epidemic can be effectively controlled as soon as possible!"
第一财经记者致电武商超市相关人士处了解到，网传的天价大白菜为有机净菜，一直是十多块钱一公斤，价格并未上涨。
The first financial reporter called Wu Shang supermarket related people learned that the net transfer of Chinese cabbage for organic vegetables, has been more than a dozen yuan a kilogram, prices have not increased.
目前超市以保供应为主，价格是随行就市，“新鲜蒜苗不比存货，现在又封城了，价格贵些也可以理解”。
At present, the supermarket to guarantee the supply, the price is on the go, "fresh garlic seedlings than inventory, now closed down, more expensive can also understand."
一位武汉市民早上去菜市场发现，大家都在抢着买菜，大白菜都没看见卖了，小白菜(小油菜)5.5元一斤，胡萝卜4.8元一斤。
Wuhan city in the morning to find that everyone is fighting to buy vegetables, cabbage did not see sold, cabbage (rape) 5.5 yuan a catty, carrots 4.8 yuan a catty.
不仅食物，医药品也成为抢手货。
Medicines as well as food are in demand.
Play▲记者：第一财经 吴绵强 周芳▲图为1月23日，市民在武汉一药店购买温度计。
The picture shows people buying thermometers at a Wuhan pharmacy on January 23.
▲图为1月23日，武汉市民在超市购买防护用品、预防药物和生活用品。
Photo: On January 23, Wuhan city people in the supermarket to buy protective supplies, preventive medicine and daily necessities.
第一财经记者到武汉市区的几家药店比如好药师大药房、惠济药店等探访，药店工作人员说，今天客流量明显比往常多，大家都集中购买防常规防护用品、预防药物以及红外体温计等，防护口罩和手套销售一空。
First financial reporters visited several pharmacies in Wuhan, such as the Good Pharmacist Pharmacy and Waiji Pharmacy, and drugstore staff said today there was a marked increase in traffic, with people focusing on routine protective equipment, preventive medicine and infrared thermometers, and selling out of face masks and gloves.
▲图为1月23日，武汉一山姆会员店，货架上的物品已卖光了。
The picture shows a Sam's store in Wuhan on January 23. Goods on the shelves had been sold out.
▲图为1月23日，武汉一山姆会员店个人用品和婴儿护理用品专区，民众排队购买物品。
Photo shows a Sam's shop in Wuhan on January 23, personal effects and baby care supplies area, people line up to buy items.
武汉一家医疗机构的一线医生说，医院急需N95口罩，护目镜，防护服，塑胶手套……，目前不仅仅我们一家单位缺，是所有的单位都短缺。
The first-line doctor at a medical facility in Wuhan said the hospital was in urgent need of N95 masks, goggles, protective clothing and plastic gloves.
一般医疗单位准备的防护服等物资，1年都不会用到现在一个小时的量。
General medical units prepared protective clothing and other supplies, a year will not use the current one-hour quantity.
▲图为1月23日，武汉市民在超市购买防护用品、预防药物和生活用品。
Photo: On January 23, Wuhan city people in the supermarket to buy protective supplies, preventive medicine and daily necessities.
一位武汉市委有关人士呼吁，大家有渠道尽快呼吁其他城市来驰援武汉，当下不能拘泥正规流程。
A Wuhan municipal government official called on people to call on other cities to come to Wuhan as soon as possible and not to adhere to the formal process.
当天，武汉市新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎指挥部发布消息称，目前，武汉市大宗商品、食品、医疗防护用品等储备充分、供应顺畅。
On the same day, Wuhan, the new coronavirus infection of the pneumonia command released news, Wuhan City, such as commodities, food, medical supplies and other reserves of adequate, smooth supply.
请广大市民不用恐慌，不必囤积，以免造成不必要的浪费。
Please do not panic, do not hoard, so as not to cause unnecessary waste.
湖北省商务厅介绍，春节期间，将继续加强粮、油、肉、蛋、菜等生活必需品市场监测，并做好应急预案，畅通主要生活必需品货源渠道，组织大型流通企业和应急商品重点联系企业适当增加库存，保障生活必需品市场供给、价格稳定，还将针对新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情，进一步做好卫生防疫工作，督促各商场超市、农贸市场严把生鲜食品进货关、加强源头追溯管控，加大消毒灭菌频次、加强环境卫生管控。
During the Spring Festival, we will continue to strengthen market monitoring of grain, oil, meat, eggs and vegetables, make emergency plans, unimpeded supply channels for major necessities, organize large circulation enterprises and key enterprises in emergency supplies, ensure stable market supply and price of life necessities.
1月21日，九州通、国药控股湖北公司、奥美医疗、稳健医疗、高德红外等10余家企业共同承诺，24小时开足马力生产，不计成本从外省空运，全力保障武汉市急需的口罩、防护服、体温检测仪等防控产品供应。
On January 21, more than 10 enterprises, including Kyushu Tong, Hubei Pharmaceutical Holding Company, Ogilvy Medical Corporation, Steady Medical Service and Gao De Infrared, pledged to produce in full capacity 24 hours at full capacity, regardless of cost, and to supply Wuhan with much-needed masks, protective clothing and body temperature detectors.
那些还在上班的人小陈是武汉一家大型互联网公司员工，春节包括他在内可能有100多人需要加班。
Chen, who is still at work, is an employee of a large Wuhan Internet company, and more than 100 people, including him, may have to work overtime for the Spring Festival holiday.
他上午告诉第一财经记者，公司刚刚开会决定，为了防控新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎，大家都回家办公。
He told the first financial reporter this morning that the company had just held a meeting to decide, in order to prevent and control the new coronavirus infection pneumonia, everyone went home.
“我们今天分行通知停止营业，现在在家里。
"Our branch is closed today and we are at home.
”一位武汉银行人士告诉记者。
A Wuhan banker told reporters.
作为武汉市的一名公务员，小布的春节几乎没有休息。
As a civil servant in Wuhan, Xiao Bu had hardly any rest during the Spring Festival.
他告诉第一财经记者，原本他只需要在春节假期值班一天，但现在是轮班倒，“一天12个小时”。
He told the first financial reporter that he had been on duty for only one day during the Spring Festival holiday, but was now on a shift, "12 hours a day."
目前，对于武汉普通市民而言，疫情的加重意味着出门的大大减少，想方设法地不去公共场合；但小布这样公务员的生活却是另外一番场景：全副武装地穿梭于办公室、公共管理区域甚至部分医院。
At present, for the average Wuhan citizen, the worsening of the epidemic means a significant reduction in travel and a desire to avoid public places; but the life of a civil servant like Xiao Bu is a different story: shuttling heavily through offices, public administration areas, and even some hospitals.
自2020年1月23日10时起，武汉市城市公交、地铁、轮渡、长途客运暂停运营。
Since 10: 00 on January 23, 2020, Wuhan city bus, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger transport suspended operation.
Play▲记者：第一财经 吴绵强因为小布自己开车上下班，所以目前不受影响，但是在公交、地铁暂停运营之后，他说没车的同事，目前还可以选择的是出租车和滴滴，或者由顺路的同事开车带到单位。
But after the suspension of bus and subway services, he said, 'My colleagues who don't have a car now have a choice of taxis and drip drops, or they can be taken to work by car by a colleague on the other side of the road.
武汉的王女士说，今天自己要去单位上班，早上街上人比较少，还有些人不戴口罩。
Ms. Wang of Wuhan said that she would go to work today, there are fewer people on the street in the morning, and some people do not wear masks.
“我早上感觉大概还有两三成的人没有戴口罩，一些人的防范意识还是不强，这也让人很担忧。
"I feel like two or three out of ten people don't wear masks this morning, and some people are still not very defensive," he said.
”小陈说。
"said Chen.
1月22日，武汉市政府通告，当日起在该市公共场所实施佩戴口罩控制措施。
On January 22, Wuhan city government announced that the same day in public places to implement mask control measures.
市民群众到商场购物、去公园散步以及乘坐公共交通工具时，须按照要求佩戴口罩。
Members of the public are required to wear masks when shopping in shopping malls, taking walks in parks and taking public transport.
拒不执行者，由各相关主管部门依法处理。
Refusal to implement shall be dealt with by relevant authorities according to law.
情节严重者，将被追究刑事责任。
In serious cases, criminal liability will be established.
通告指出，佩戴口罩控制措施实施范围包括宾馆、美容店、影剧院、公园、图书馆、商场、公共交通工具以及其他人群聚集的公共场所等8个类别。
Eight categories of mask control measures include hotels, beauty parlours, theaters, parks, libraries, shopping malls, public transport and other public places where people congregate, the notice said.
【推荐阅读】新病毒传播渠道都没搞清，慎言“可防可控”。
New virus transmission channels are not clear, careful to say "preventable controllable."
